ch.ecma.csta.logical

Class LogicalDeviceFeatureAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.ecma.csta.logical.LogicalDeviceFeatureAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    LogicalDeviceFeatureListener, java.util.EventListener

    public class LogicalDeviceFeatureAdapter
extends java.lang.Object
implements LogicalDeviceFeatureListener
    Implements a "do nothing" callback method for each logical device feature event type. To learn more about how to use a listener adapter, see Using Listeners in the Device, Media & Call Control (DMCC) API.
    Version:
    4.1
    Author:
    Avaya Inc.

      • agentLoggedOff

        public void agentLoggedOff(AgentLoggedOffEvent event)
        Description copied from interface: LogicalDeviceFeatureListener
        Supported in AES 6.1 and later.

        A callback function which is automatically invoked on a listener previously added to a device when the AgentLoggedOffEvent occurs on that device.

        The AgentLoggedOffEvent indicates that an agent has logged off an ACD device or an ACD group. See AgentLoggedOffEvent for more information.

        Optional parameters are available in the private data area with an Avaya-specified AgentLoggedOffEventPrivateData object.

        The device parameter of the AgentLoggedOffEvent structure is of type SubjectDeviceID so extracting the device ID is a two-step process:
        Example: 

         // get the DeviceID
 SubjectDeviceID subjDeviceID = event.getAgentDevice();
 DeviceID deviceID = subjDeviceID.getDeviceIdentifier();

 // now get the agentId and the acdGroup
 String agentId = event.getAgentID();
 DeviceID acdGroup = event.getAcdGroup();
 
 // now get the private data from the event
 if (event.getExtensions() != null {
     Object privDataObject = event.getExtensions().getSinglePrivateData();
     if (privDataObject instanceof AgentLoggedOffEventPrivateData) {
         // get the reasonCode for the agent logging off
         short reasonCode = (AgentLoggedOffEventPrivateData)privDataObject.getReasonCode();
         // based on the value of the reason code, do something
     }
 }
        Specified by:
        agentLoggedOff in interface LogicalDeviceFeatureListener
        Parameters:
        event - provides data about the agent logging off of a device.

      • doNotDisturb

        public void doNotDisturb(DoNotDisturbEvent event)
        Description copied from interface: LogicalDeviceFeatureListener
        A callback function which is automatically invoked on a listener previously added to a device when the DoNotDisturbEvent occurs on that device.

        The DoNotDisturbEvent indicates that the do not disturb feature has been changed for a device. See DoNotDisturbEvent for more information.

        The device parameter of the DoNotDisturbEvent structure is of type SubjectDeviceID so extracting the device ID is a two-step process: 

         SubjectDeviceID subjDeviceID = event.getDevice();
 DeviceID deviceID = subjDeviceID.getDeviceIdentifier();
        Example: 
         // device where the do not disturb feature was changed
 DeviceID deviceID = event.getDevice().getDeviceIdentifier();
 //get the DND status
 boolean dndStatus = event.getDoNotDisturbOn();

      • agentLoginExtensionEvent

        public void agentLoginExtensionEvent(AgentLoginExtensionEvent event)
        Description copied from interface: LogicalDeviceFeatureListener
        Supported in AES 6.1 and later.

        A callback function which is automatically invoked on a listener previously added to a device in response to a GetAgentLogin request.

        The AgentLoginExtensionEvent is a CSTAPrivateEvent that contains a list. The list contains the number of extensions in the message and up to 10 extensions of ACD agents logged into the ACD split. The entire sequence of agentLoginExtensionEvent may contain a large volume of information (up to the maximum number of logged-in agents allowed in an ACD Split). The final agentLoginExtensionEvent specifies that it contains zero extensions and the isFinalResponse parameter is set to true which serves to inform the application that no more messages will be sent in response to this query.

        A listener must first be added on the ACD split for the session that will issue the GetAgentLogin request. The agentLoginExtensionEvent is published only on the listener associated with the session that issued the GetAgentLogin request. Other sessions that have a listener for the same ACD split will not receive the agentLoginExtensionEvent events.

        See AgentLoginExtensionEvent for more information.

        Example: 

         AgentLoginExtensionList agentList = event.getAgentLoginExtensionList();
 for (int x =0; x < agentList.getAgentExtensionCount(); x++) { 
     String agent = agentList.getAgentExtension(x);
     System.out.println("AgentExtension in event=" + agent);
 }
 System.out.println("isFinalResponse=" + event.getIsFinalResponse());   
 if (event.getIsFinalResponse()) {
     try {
         cleanup();
     } catch (CstaException e) {
         e.printStackTrace();
     }
 }
        Specified by:
        agentLoginExtensionEvent in interface LogicalDeviceFeatureListener
        Parameters:
        event - provides the status of the forwarding feature for a device
